---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
import { profile } from '../data/profile';
import { v23Identity } from '../data/v23';
const principles=[
  ['Start with the decision','Define who acts, what evidence they need, and what authority the system can hold before choosing a model.'],
  ['Keep uncertainty visible','Calibration, citations, failed rules, missing data, and reviewer disagreement belong in the product—not a hidden evaluation notebook.'],
  ['Build the operating path','Data contracts, deployment, telemetry, fallback, and adoption are part of the model’s job description.'],
  ['Prefer proof over theater','A green test, reproducible artifact, honest limit, or measured workflow change says more than a speculative architecture diagram.'],
  ['Lead across boundaries','The useful work happens between domain experts, operations, data, engineering, product, security, and the people accountable for outcomes.'],
];
const structuredData = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'ProfilePage',
  name: 'About Shailesh Dudala',
  description: 'How Shailesh Dudala approaches applied AI, predictive ML, document intelligence, MLOps, product leadership, and accountable agent systems.',
  mainEntity: {
    '@type': 'Person',
    name: profile.name,
    jobTitle: profile.role,
    url: 'https://shaileshdudala.com/about/',
    sameAs: [profile.github, profile.linkedin],
  },
};
---
<Layout title="About — Shailesh Dudala" description="How Shailesh Dudala approaches applied AI, predictive ML, document intelligence, MLOps, product leadership, and accountable agent systems." canonicalPath="/about/" jsonLd={structuredData}>
  <section class="v23-page-hero about-v23-hero"><div class="shell"><p class="v23-kicker">ABOUT / {v23Identity.name}</p><div><h1>I build at the boundary between model behavior and human consequence.</h1><p>{v23Identity.shortBio}</p></div></div></section>
  <section class="v23-section about-origin"><div class="shell about-origin-grid"><div class="about-monogram" aria-hidden="true"><span>SD</span><i></i><i></i><i></i></div><div><p class="v23-kicker">Origin</p><h2>Biomedical informatics made ambiguity concrete.</h2><p>Clinical and scientific data taught me that a technically correct result can still fail when lineage, assumptions, timing, or operating context are invisible.</p><p>That lesson followed the work outward—from statistical models to healthcare products, local document systems, and agents whose actions need contracts, evidence, and explicit authority.</p><blockquote>“The goal is not to remove people from consequential work. It is to give them a better system for seeing, deciding, and learning.”</blockquote></div></div></section>
  <section class="v23-section principles-v23"><div class="shell v23-section-heading"><div><p class="v23-kicker">Working principles</p><h2>How I turn uncertainty into delivery.</h2></div><p>These principles connect the whole portfolio without forcing every project into one technology taxonomy.</p></div><div class="shell principle-ledger">{principles.map(([title,body],index)=><article><span>{String(index+1).padStart(2,'0')}</span><h3>{title}</h3><p>{body}</p></article>)}</div></section>
  <section class="v23-section leadership-v23"><div class="shell leadership-grid"><div><p class="v23-kicker">Leadership</p><h2>Translate, align, and leave a system others can operate.</h2></div><div><p>I work across strategy and implementation: clarifying the decision, shaping the data and model path, defining acceptance evidence, and helping teams own what ships.</p><ul><li>Frame ambiguous problems as testable operating contracts.</li><li>Connect model metrics to capacity, workflow, risk, and product decisions.</li><li>Make failure modes discussable across technical and non-technical teams.</li><li>Build public-safe explanations without exposing private systems or data.</li></ul></div></div></section>
  <section class="v23-section about-now"><div class="shell"><p class="v23-kicker">Now</p><h2>Production agentic AI—grounded in the full applied-ML arc.</h2><p>Current work focuses on claims and document agents. Open source explores execution harnesses, representation engineering, healthcare interoperability, forecasting, and local AI. Those are supporting proof systems, not the whole identity.</p><div><a href="/work/">Professional work ↗</a><a href="/lab/">Project Lab ↗</a><a href="/research/">Research ↗</a></div></div></section>
  <section class="v23-contact"><div class="shell"><p class="v23-kicker">Contact</p><h2>Have a consequential workflow that needs more than a model demo?</h2><p>Let’s talk about the architecture between evidence and action.</p><div><a class="v23-button primary" href={`mailto:${profile.email}`}>Email Shailesh ↗</a><a href={profile.linkedin}>LinkedIn ↗</a><a href={profile.github}>GitHub ↗</a></div></div></section>
</Layout>
